      "ItemId": "https://ardalis.com/genai-is-the-new-offshoring/",
      "Title": "GenAI is the new Offshoring",
      "PublishDate": "2025-06-06T00:00:00+00:00",
      "Summary": "<blockquote>\n<p>I originally <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/ardalis.com/post/3lpf22jfrbs2d\">posted this on LinkedIn / BlueSky</a> but I&rsquo;ve found that it&rsquo;s nearly impossible to find (searching for &ldquo;AI is the new offshoring&rdquo; or&quot;genAI is the new offshoring&quot; both fail to find it) so I&rsquo;m cross-posting here and adding a bit more context.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Twenty years ago, the internet and improved communications led to a massive push in US corporate enterprises to outsource IT and dev efforts to far less expensive offshore outfits staffed by eager but often inexperienced workers making pennies on the dollar compared to their US counterparts. Layoffs occurred in many orgs and whole departments moved offshore in some cases, and while there were success stories and many companies continue to leverage offshore talent, many (most in my experience but that&rsquo;s probably biased by the ones coming to my company for help) later regretted the decision.</p>",
      "Content": null,
      "Language": "en-us",
      "Link": "https://ardalis.com/genai-is-the-new-offshoring/"
