      "FeedId": "https://ardalis.com/index.xml",
      "ItemId": "https://ardalis.com/genai-coding-investment-risk-strategy/",
      "Title": "Managing GenAI Coding Risk Like an Investment",
      "PublishDate": "2025-06-05T00:00:00+00:00",
      "Summary": "<p>Generative AI tools have greatly improved in their ability to generate large amounts of code, quickly, to support software development tasks. They&rsquo;re fast, confident, and in some cases even creative. But they&rsquo;re also fallible, occasionally destructive, and always somewhat unpredictable.</p>\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve ever used GenAI to bang out a prototype in hours instead of days, you&rsquo;ve seen the upside. If you&rsquo;ve watched it delete critical files, misconfigure infrastructure, or hallucinate complex nonsense that passes code review but fails in production, you&rsquo;ve felt the downside.</p>",
      "Content": null,
      "Language": "en-us",
      "Link": "https://ardalis.com/genai-coding-investment-risk-strategy/"
    },
